Data Structures
Dictionary (my_dict) → shows methods like keys(), values(), items(), get(), and update() to access and modify key‑value pairs.
List (my_list) → demonstrates append(), remove(), index(), sort(), and reverse() for ordered collections.
Tuple (my_tuple) → only supports count() and index() because tuples are immutable (cannot be changed).
Set (my_set) → shows add(), remove(), union(), intersection(), and clear() for unique, unordered elements.

Conditionals
If → checks a single condition.
If‑Else → executes one block if true, another if false.
If‑Elif‑Else → multiple condition checks.
Nested If‑Else → condition inside another condition.

Loop Control
Break → exits loop early.
Continue → skips current iteration.
Pass → placeholder, does nothing but keeps structure valid.

Input & Built‑in Functions
input() → takes user input.
range() → generates a sequence of numbers.
len() → returns length of a collection.
type() → shows data type.

Loops
For loop → iterates over a sequence.
While loop → repeats until condition becomes false.
